[ROLE leader][STAGE pre-lead] Lead the \CT, the top of your \CT9 sequence within \CT9754 — a safe lead against the slam.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE auction-end] You are in 6NT and need twelve. Count the winners: five top spades in the \SAKQJT6, four top clubs (\CAKQJ), two top diamonds (\DAK), and the \HA come to twelve straight off the top, with the long diamonds as extra. NS hold 32 of the 40, so the defenders have only 8 and neither bid. A club finesse is available, but you already count twelve, so just cash carefully.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-lead] West led the \CT, which looks like top of a sequence and rides into your strong clubs. Count to twelve: five spades, four clubs, \DAK, and the \HA are all there — the slam is cold without a finesse. Win the club, cash your spades and clubs, and take the diamonds; do not finesse a club into East, who rates to hold the heart honours and must stay off lead. Counting first shows the finesse adds nothing you need.

[ROLE declarer][STAGE post-play] You counted before playing and saw twelve on top, which made the club finesse a needless risk. Nicely played — you cashed your winners in order and kept the danger hand out.}
